Description.SourceString: Before he became a Mayor, he used to run his own general store with his late wife, Carol.
A local carpenter who lives in the Hillside. Joko has a family in a neighboring island and visits them every here and there.
He runs Socket Electronics and his family business, Hillside Vineyard. Known for being a foodie and his tendency to overthink things.
She spent years doing Universal Doctors Program around the world where she receives little to no pay before settling down in Coral Island. Likes to play chess & pool.
Ben has an extensive collection of healing crystals and loves road trips. He indulges his money on music festivals.
A hunter. She spends her day guarding the mouth of the forest, keeping an eye on the cavern. She doesn’t celebrate birthdays.
He owns and runs the general store. Sam spends his free time doing brain exercises such as chess, jigsaw, crossword puzzles, and the like.
She works remotely for a cybersecurity company and has no set working hours. Lily likes solitude and miniature bonsais.
He is the island’s rancher and lives in a humble cabin in the forest with his family. Doesn’t celebrate birthdays.
Alice runs the inn in between her readings. She likes discussing unexplainable phenomenons and studied a little bit about them back in university.
A wildlife enthusiast. When Anne is not busy editing videos, she enjoys going to the beach and submerges herself in nature.
He loves animals and sometimes can be found in the vineyard playing with Taco. He wants to be a vet one day.
Betty spends her retirement days going around town re-filling bird feeders, educating kids about coral reefs, and baking patisseries.
She owns the Hillside Vineyard. A model turned housewife, turned farmer, Bree, spends her days doing quality control, and being an excellent homemaker.
A local doctor. He uses his free time to catch up with the islanders at the tavern or just go around giving out medical advice.
Local carpenter. In her free time, she tends her herb garden and busies herself with community activities. Carpentry is a passion she said, not a job.
Dippa likes to lose themselves to make art. As they once said, sanity is boring, and to them, boring is not living.‬
A hairdresser. She likes to scavenge around the lake for fresh berries/mushrooms and has a heart for vintage items.
She lives a quiet life and is not a big fan of night-outs. Emma is very proud of her food truck.
When she isn’t working, she can be found volunteering at school, or around town lending her ears to those in need, free of charge.
Eva enjoys talking to the islanders-- local, new, visitors, everybody--and is good friends with a lot of them. A talented baker.
He runs the tavern with his brother, Noah. Loves cooking and vintage scooters. He has 2 very spoiled cats, Peanut and Butter.
He helps Sunny run the Beach Shack as a cook. Jim makes a killer smoke salmon that he sometimes sells at the shack.
He’s lived in Coral Island his whole life and has fostered close relationships with other islanders; be it people, animals, trees, spirits from the beyond--all of them.
She is a self-hired, yoga instructor at the community center and an influencer. She spends her day going around the island with a camera on hand.
A marine biologist. She dedicates her life in a study to improve coral reefs and developing ways to improve the island with sea minerals.
Macy grew up on a neighboring island. Her passion is in photography, animals, and nature. Enjoys simple nights.
Millie works at the library and oversees the museum. She spends her free time bird watching and restoring old books.
The villa at the beach is one of her many vacation homes. She is well educated, humble, and a flirt in nature. Enjoys lavish vacations.
He spends his days keeping the tavern running. On rare occasions that he is free, he enjoys long walks and discussing theories on unexplainable phenomenons.
He loves detective shows and wants to join the law force when he grows up. Dream to be a police detective.
A local blacksmith. Charismatic. He can be found around town, lending hands to the islanders, cleaning up the graveyard, or tossing anecdotes at the tavern.
A wildlife enthusiast. Along with his wife, the couple makes a documentary about wildlife for a living. Big heart, likes the beach.
A local blacksmith. Rafael is reserved and prefers silence, something that he considers a luxury in his line of work.
Randy Barnes. A teacher with a remarkable ability to explain complex ideas in a simple and easy to understand manner. Loves classic literature.
He is always up for fun and is never a bore. He found his passion for artifacts and has dedicated his life to it.
Along with her twin sister, Alice, they run the inn. Suki is a mom first, and anything else second. A fan of healthy living.
He runs the Beach Shack. Though he doesn’t fish often anymore, one can still see pictures of his monster fish catches at his house upstairs.
A marine biologist. He works at the laboratory on the weekdays and spends his free time hanging out with his friends.
A dog. Lives in Hillside Vineyard.
A local fisherman. He spends most of his days fishing or playing guitar. On the weekends, he makes a quick buck at the tavern, performing live.
Valentina enjoys tea parties and trying out new things. She lives at the inn and often plays at the beach.
A former high-flying lawyer. He now owns the Hillside Vineyard, the mansion in the back and some shops downtown.
She is a wildlife enthusiast, just like her parents. She enjoys a game of volleyball, bird watching, and winters.
She is an adventurer at heart. She enjoys going around the island and finding treasures; be it gems, old artifacts, or a buried history
